    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-04-05T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-04-05T14:00:00-05:00" n="70"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d70">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.00/995: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-05T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 5, 1941—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>217. The Department suggests that a conversation at this time with the principal
                        official<note n="77" xml:id="d70fn77">Baron Hiranuma.</note> mentioned in
                    your telegram 123, January 27, 4 p.m., if feasible and in your discretion
                    appropriate, might be productive of helpful information.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
